modules.description: Reads a file as a template, injecting content and variables using a specified data injectable module. Operates on path structures and returns task-composed tuples of data and strings. Used to dynamically generate content from template files with variable substitution.

Provides functions to manage and execute build processes, including initializing a development environment and triggering builds. Operates with configuration settings and project metadata stored in local files. Used to set up isolated OCaml projects and compile them using Dune.

Loads and processes template files by substituting variables and content using a data injectable module, operating on path structures. It handles data and string outputs as task-composed tuples, enabling dynamic content generation. Templates can include conditional blocks, loops, and variable interpolation based on provided data. For example, generating personalized emails or HTML pages from a single template by injecting user-specific data.
